rigin, and for the two smaller drift\ntimescales (10kyr and 100kyr). For less abundant ice species, and the longest\ndrift timescale (1Myr), the changes are larger. Pebble drift chemistry\ngenerally increases the ice abundances of CO$_{2}$, HCN and SO, at the expense\nof decreasing abundances of other volatile molecules.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Aug 2022 18:07:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-14"}
